        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">David Chen, Alpine Mortgage in Denver, independent broker 6 years. Struggling to generate consistent applications despite competitive rates. Website: template from 2017, outdated design, NMLS # buried in footer, no current rates, no loan calculator, "contact us for rates" only, application form not mobile-friendly, no lender logos, minimal compliance badges. Results: 12 applications/month, 8 funded loans/month, $24,000/month revenue (enough to survive, not grow). Competitors with professional sites: 60+ applications/month. Losing ideal buyers who never apply because can't see legitimacy. Tried Facebook ads: expensive, low quality leads. The problem: not his rates or service - the website fails to build trust.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-emerald-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-emerald-50/50 rounded-r mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX: REBUILT WITH WEBFLOW AI - COMPLIANT PROFESSIONAL SITE, RATES VISIBLE, CALCULATOR</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I rebuilt his site with Webflow AI in 3 days. New compliant professional site: "NMLS #284751" badge prominently in hero, "Today's Rates: 6.5% 30-Year Fixed" updated daily via CMS, interactive mortgage calculator, mobile-optimized application form, "We Work With: 50+ Lenders" with logos (Wells Fargo, Chase, Quicken, etc), "Equal Housing Lender" and "NMLS Consumer Access" compliance badges, loan programs clearly defined (Conventional, FHA, VA, Jumbo), fast pre-qualification promise, client testimonials. Webflow delivered custom NMLS compliance controls, professional design, fast PageSpeed (97), CMS for rate updates. Cost: $42/month.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-emerald-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-emerald-50/50 rounded-r mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER (90 DAYS): 68 APPLICATIONS/MONTH, 467% INCREASE</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Month 1 results: 42 applications (up from 12, 250% increase), 24 funded loans (up from 8, 200% increase), $72,000 revenue (up from $24,000, 200% increase). Google ranking: page 1 position 5 for "Denver mortgage broker." Mortgage calculator: most-used feature, average 3:42 time on page, 67% who use calculator submit application. Mobile visitors: 73% (application fully responsive). Rate inquiries: 38/month vs 8 before (rates now visible). David: "NMLS visible = legitimacy = trust = apply. Rates visible = competitive = serious buyer. Calculator = engage = understand = apply. Lender logos = options = competitive = work with me." Month 3: 68 applications/month, 32 funded loans/month, $96,000 monthly revenue. Revenue increase: $72,000/month on $42/month investment. ROI: 171,000% in 90 days.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-sky-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-sky-50/50 rounded-r">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-sky-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN: MORTGAGE BROKER TRANSFORMATION</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Days 1-3: Site rebuild with Webflow AI, NMLS prominent, rates visible, calculator added. Days 4-14: Google indexed new pages, ranking position 30. Days 15-30: First applications from rate visibility, 42 total (vs 12 before), calculator usage high. Days 31-60: 55 applications/month, added loan officer for demand, funded loans doubled. Days 61-90: 68 applications/month, hired 2nd loan officer, expanded to refinance specialization. Net result: $72,000/month increase in revenue on $42/month investment. The lesson: Mortgage = trust business. NMLS visible = legitimate = trust = apply. Rates visible = competitive = serious = apply. Calculator = engage = understand = apply. Lenders visible = options = competitive = work with you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#EFF6FF]">
